urls.description: Norfolk Rivers Trust and the Norfolk Non-Native Species Initiative (NNNSI) have joined forces to reduce, and where possible, eliminate Himalayan balsam from the Wensum catchment, as part of a 5-year project funded by Anglian Water. Himalayan balsam (Impatiens glandulifera) is an invasive non-native species (INNS) that can spread rapidly along waterc ourses and out-compete native plants.
